#: src/mathlib.c:788
msgid "Mathlib Benchmark Help"
msgstr "Mathlib-benchmarkhjælp"

#: src/mathlib.c:790
msgid ""
"Jobs are forked and run in parallel by xnec2c, whereas threads are used by "
"the mathlib implementation to parallelize the linear algebra calculation of "
"one job.  For parallel algorithms you can reduce the number of threads in "
"use by the algorithm with the following environment variables:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS thread limit\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP thread limit\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL thread limit\n"
"\n"
"Each benchmark specifies a complexity to indicate approximately how long it "
"will take to run.  For example, O(N) means the time will scale with N and "
"O(N*J) means it will scale with N*J:\n"
"  * N is the number of mathlibs selected here:\n"
"      File->Mathlib Benchmarks->Selected Mathlibs\n"
"  * J is the number of jobs specified on the command line with -j (eg, -j "
"8)\n"
"\n"
"Higher complexity options run more benchmarks to provide additional "
"information about how you might optimize your xnec2c runtime.  The benchmark "
"menu options are as follows:  \n"
"\n"
"* Parallel (-j N): O(N/J) time: Benchmark each mathlib in parallel with the "
"number of jobs specified on the command line with -j.\n"
"\n"
"* Single Job (-j 1): O(N) time: Benchmark each mathlib with a single job "
"even if -j was specified on the command line. This is useful to find the "
"fastest interactive mathlib that is used when the frequency is changed in "
"the UI by changing a Frequency MHz +/- widget or (right-)clicking on the "
"frequency plot\n"
"\n"
"* Iterate -j N/=2: O(N*log2(J)) time: Benchmark each mathlib in parallel "
"initially with the number of jobs specified on the command line with -j, and "
"then reduce the number jobs by half for each subsequent iteration until only "
"one job remains.  This is useful to find a balance between the number of "
"parallel jobs specified by -j and the number of threads used by the linear "
"algebra library as modified by the environment variables listed above.\n"
"\n"
"* Iterate -j N-=2: O(N*J) time: Same as -j N/=2 above, but instead decrement "
"the number of jobs by 1.  This takes the longest to run.\n"
msgstr ""
"Jobs forgrenes og køres parallelt af xnec2c, hvorimod tråde bruges af "
"mathlib-implementeringen til at parallelisere den lineære algebraberegning "
"af ét job. For parallelle algoritmer kan du reducere antallet af tråde brugt "
"af algoritmen med følgende miljøvariabler:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS-trådgrænse\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP-trådgrænse\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL-trådgrænse\n"
"\n"
"Hvert benchmark angiver en kompleksitet for at indikere cirka hvor lang tid "
"det tager at køre. For eksempel betyder O(N) at tiden skalerer med N og "
"O(N*J) betyder at den skalerer med N*J:\n"
"  * N er antallet af mathlibs valgt her:\n"
"      File->Mathlib Benchmarks->Selected Mathlibs\n"
"  * J er antallet af jobs angivet på kommandolinjen med -j (f.eks. -j 8)\n"
"\n"
"Højere kompleksitetsindstillinger kører flere benchmarks for at give "
"yderligere information om hvordan du kan optimere din xnec2c-kørselstid. "
"Benchmark-menuindstillingerne er som følger:  \n"
"\n"
"* Parallel (-j N): O(N/J) tid: Benchmark af hvert mathlib parallelt med "
"antallet af jobs angivet på kommandolinjen med -j.\n"
"\n"
"* Enkelt job (-j 1): O(N) tid: Benchmark af hvert mathlib med et enkelt job "
"selv hvis -j var angivet på kommandolinjen. Dette er nyttigt for at finde "
"det hurtigste interaktive mathlib der bruges når frekvensen ændres i "
"brugerfladen ved at ændre en Frekvens MHz +/- widget eller (højre-)klikke på "
"frekvensplottet\n"
"\n"
"* Iterér -j N/=2: O(N*log2(J)) tid: Benchmark af hvert mathlib parallelt "
"startende med antallet af jobs angivet på kommandolinjen med -j, og derefter "
"reducér antallet af jobs til halvdelen for hver efterfølgende iteration "
"indtil kun ét job er tilbage. Dette er nyttigt for at finde en balance "
"mellem antallet af parallelle jobs angivet af -j og antallet af tråde brugt "
"af det lineære algebrabibliotek som ændret af miljøvariablerne angivet "
"ovenfor.\n"
"\n"
"* Iterér -j N-=2: O(N*J) tid: Samme som -j N/=2 ovenfor, men nedsæt i stedet "
"antallet af jobs med 1. Dette tager længst tid at køre.\n"

#: src/mathlib.c:839 src/mathlib.c:846 src/mathlib.c:852 src/mathlib.c:869
#: src/mathlib.c:874 src/mathlib.c:989
msgid "Mathlib Benchmark"
msgstr "Mathlib-benchmark"

#: src/mathlib.c:840
msgid "Benchmarks are disabled while optimization is activated."
msgstr "Benchmarks er deaktiveret mens optimering er aktiveret."

#: src/mathlib.c:847
msgid "You must load a NEC2 input file before running benchmarks."
msgstr "Du skal indlæse en NEC2-inputfil før kørsel af benchmarks."

#: src/mathlib.c:853
msgid ""
"Choosing a benchmark other than \"Single Job\" has no effect unless -j is "
"specified on the command line."
msgstr ""
"Valg af et benchmark ud over \"Single Job\" har ingen effekt medmindre -j er "
"angivet på kommandolinjen."

#: src/mathlib.c:870
msgid "You must select at least one math library to benchmark"
msgstr "Du skal vælge mindst ét matematikbibliotek til benchmark"

#: src/mathlib.c:875
#, c-format
msgid ""
"This will run a frequency loop benchmark for each detected linear algebra "
"library and then provide a summary.  It may take some time to complete "
"depending on how big and how many frequencies your NEC2 will use. Detailed "
"timing will be provided in the terminal.\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"* Only one Intel MKL library can be tested without restarting xnec2c, so "
"select which one you wish to benchmark before proceeding or it will choose "
"the first in the list and skip the rest.\n"
"\n"
"* Thread congestion will occur for multi-threaded libraries when using the -"
"j N option if there are not enough CPUs available to accommodate the forked "
"processes in combination with library threads.  Consider reducing the value "
"of -j N for benchmarking to find what library works best with a mix of "
"forking and threading; you can use `top` to monitor your CPU usageand if it "
"reaches 0%% idle then you might consider reducing -j N.\n"
"\n"
"You may wish to experiment setting these environment variables:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS thread limit\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP thread limit\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL thread limit\n"
"\n"
"Click OK to proceed, this dialog will close when complete."
msgstr ""
"Dette vil køre et frekvensløkke-benchmark for hvert fundet lineært "
"algebrabibliotek og derefter vise en opsummering. Det kan tage noget tid "
"afhængigt af hvor stor og hvor mange frekvenser din NEC2-fil bruger. "
"Detaljeret tidsmåling vises i terminalen.\n"
"\n"
"Bemærkninger:\n"
"* Kun ét Intel MKL-bibliotek kan testes uden at genstarte xnec2c, vælg "
"derfor hvilket du ønsker at benchmarke inden du fortsætter, ellers vælges "
"det første på listen og resten springes over.\n"
"\n"
"* Trådkollision vil forekomme for multitrådede biblioteker ved brug af -j N-"
"indstillingen hvis der ikke er tilstrækkeligt med CPU'er til at håndtere de "
"forgrenede processer i kombination med bibliotekstråde. Overvej at reducere "
"værdien af -j N ved benchmarking for at finde hvilket bibliotek fungerer "
"bedst med en blanding af forgrening og trådning; du kan bruge `top` til at "
"overvåge din CPU-brug, og hvis den når 0%% inaktiv bør du overveje at "
"reducere -j N.\n"
"\n"
"Du kan eventuelt eksperimentere med disse miljøvariabler:\n"
"  * OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=N\t# OpenBLAS-trådgrænse\n"
"  * OMP_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# OpenMP-trådgrænse\n"
"  * MKL_NUM_THREADS=N\t\t# Intel MKL-trådgrænse\n"
"\n"
"Klik OK for at fortsætte, denne dialog lukkes, når det er færdigt."

